description: Introducing the IPL
---
<div>
  <h2 class="title">What?</h2>
  The <b>Illinois Programming League (IPL)</b>, a series of ICPC-style programming contest open to all UIUC students. Keep excelling in the contests and claim the rewards!
  <br><br>
  Don't forget to fill up our registration form! You can do it anytime in the semester.
</div>


<h1>When and Where?</h1>
<b>Every Monday, 7-9 PM, Room 0218 (basement), Siebel Center</b>

<h1>Why?</h1>
It's fun! The IPL is a perfect opportunity for people who enjoy solving challenging algorithmic programming problems. Competing in the IPL will greatly boost your skills and help you ace in classes and interviews. Also get ready to meet some of the strongest programmers in the university! (Plus, food every week and prizes over $1000!)

<h1>Schedule</h1>
<b>Registration:</b> anytime during the semester <br>
<b>Weekly Meeting:</b> 7:00 - 9:00 PM CDT, every Monday <br>
<b>Contests:</b> lasts for 1.5 to 2 hours during the meeting

<h1>Food</h1>
<b>Free food</b> will be offered before every contest. (contestants only)

<h1>Prizes</h1>
